<TITLE> Fire at Uttara leads to hour-long gridlock </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com)Two shops in Uttara Rajuk Market were gutted by fire on Saturday, leading to an hour-long traffic gridlock along the Uttara section of Airport Road as huge crowds gathered to watch the spectacle. The fire brigade brought the situation under control an hour after a fire caught hold in two shops adjacent to the market's main entrance, Altaf Hossain, assistant sub-inspector of Uttara Police Station, told bdnews24.com. He said so many people crowded the area to watch the fire brigade in action that a massive tailback ensued on Airport Road. bdne
